olive oil
1 packet portabello mushrooms
1 packet fresh lasagne sheet
1 packet Soffritto Mix
1 packet diced bacon
1 packet beef mince
1 packet garlic paste
¼ cup water
1 packet tomato sugo
1 packet bechamel sauce
1 bag baby broccoli
1 packet green beans
1 packet basil pesto
1 packet flaked almonds
1 sachet Aussie Spice Blend
1 packet Grated Parmesan Cheese
1 packet Shredded Cheddar Cheese
1 packet chocolate brownie mix
1 packet white chocolate chips
1 packet peanut butter
1 packet berry compote

• Preheat oven to 220°C/200°C fan-forced.
Thinly slice portabello mushrooms. Slice fresh
lasagne sheet in half widthways.
• Heat a large frying pan over high heat with a
drizzle of olive oil. Cook mushrooms, soffritto
mix and diced bacon, breaking up with a spoon,
until tender and golden, 6-8 minutes. Transfer
to a bowl.

• Return the frying pan to high heat with a drizzle
of olive oil. Cook beef mince, breaking up with a
spoon, until browned, 3-4 minutes.
• Add garlic paste and Aussie spice blend, then
return the bacon and veggies to the pan and
cook, stirring, until fragrant, 1-2 minutes.
• Add the water and tomato sugo and cook until
slightly reduced, 1-2 minutes.

• Meanwhile, combine bechamel sauce and
grated Parmesan cheese in a medium bowl.
Season with pepper.

• Spoon half the filling into a baking dish, then
top with a layer of lasagne sheets (lay two
sheets alongside each other for 4 people). Follow
with a layer of cheesy sauce.
• Repeat with the remaining filling, lasagne
sheets and cheesy sauce. Top evenly with
shredded Cheddar cheese.
• Bake lasagne until golden, 20-25 minutes.

• Meanwhile, roughly chop baby broccoli. Trim
ends of green beans.
• Wipe out frying pan and return to medium-high
heat. Cook baby broccoli and green beans until
tender, 5-6 minutes. Season to taste.

TIP: Add a dash of water to the pan to help the
veggies cook.

• Divide monster beef and bacon lasagne between
plates.
• Cut off one corner of the basil pesto packet and
draw a fun face on the lasagne. Assemble green
beans and baby broccoli as hair and flaked
almonds as teeth for the monster. Enjoy!